benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles - Retrieve a bundle by external key

covered: Valid Request scenarios (successful retrievals, including deleted/not-deleted, audit variations) across multiple TC cases.
Query Parameter variations tested extensively (externalKey, includedDeleted, audit) including invalid values and edge cases.
Error handling and status codes covered (400 for invalid input, 404 for not found, 503 for service issues).
Negative scenarios and data integrity checks (non-existent keys, empty results, multiple bundles with same key, non-ASCII keys, long/short keys).
Performance and resilience aspects (response time, concurrency, transient failures, recovery).
Compatibility and data format checks (JSON response, required fields, backward compatibility).
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not covered (no explicit tests for paging through results).
Caching behavior (ETag, Cache-Control headers) is not tested.
Rate limiting/throttling for rapid consecutive requests is not tested.
Explicit tests for handling of service outages separate from dependency failures (beyond 503 responses) could be clarified.
Tests for unusual or malformed input patterns beyond those already included (e.g., more varied injection attempts) could be expanded.
recommendations: Add dedicated pagination tests to ensure correct behavior and performance when listing many bundles (page size, page tokens, total count).
Add tests validating caching headers and behavior (ETag validation, If-None-Match, Cache-Control) to ensure proper client-side caching semantics.
Introduce rate limiting/throttling scenarios to confirm proper 429 handling or backoff behavior under load.
Differentiate service downtime vs dependency failure tests with explicit scenarios to ensure consistent 503 handling under varied failure modes.
Augment edge-case coverage for input formats (additional unusual characters in externalKey, more Unicode edge cases) and verify no leakage of internal error details.
